B. It shall be unlawful to do any of the following on or within
1
2
the Kiamichi River from four (4) miles north of the Highway 3 bridge
2
3
intersection to the Arkansas state line or the Glover River from its
3
4
confluence with the Little River to its branch into the east and
4
5
west creek:
5
6
1. Divert water, including industrial water, for nonlocal
6
7
municipalities or counties for the purposes of sale, profit, power
7
8
generation, or battery or data storage;
8
9
2. Divert water for nonlocal agricultural purposes;
9
10
3. Build any dams, impoundments, or diversion structures; or
10
11
4. Perform local farming or ranching, silviculture, forestry,
11
12
or other agricultural uses and practices.
12
13
C. This section shall not apply to existing practices or
13
14
structures before the effective date of this act.
